<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894292>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 2: Phaeophila dendroides. A: Tufts growing on the thallus of Acetabularia crenulata (arrows). B: Detail of a tuft with uniseriate filaments composed of cylindrical cells. C: Filaments with cylindrical and spherical cells in in vitro culture. D: Cells with erect, colorless and sinuous hairs (arrows). E: Detail of the dilated base of the hair (arrow). F: Cells with characteristic intumescences (arrows). G: Detail of a cell with parietal chloroplast with pyrenoids. H: Gametes or spores." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4894292/files/figure.png" .

